    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a fair point about the administrative gaps. But there's something else that's bothering me. When I look at the specific locations where these \"vanishing\" communities were located, they are almost always in very dense, difficult-to-reach terrain—like thickest parts of the woods or near deep limestone caves. It's almost like they're choosing places where it would be impossible for a census taker to actually find them. Could there be any other reason why a group would intentionally hide in those specific, isolated environments?",
